  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and a screening sensitivity study were performed to identify dominant input parameters. All 13 credibility factors are evaluated; 7 factors are assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors are not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). The screening sensitivity exercise—carried out informally as part of the Monte Carlo UQ workflow—identified rotor tip clearance and blood viscosity as dominant contributors to hemolysis index variance; however, no structured SensitivityAnalysis record was generated from this exercise. Decision: Accepted pending additional validation data.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
