      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis index comparison against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index values compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump test dataset across 5 flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error of 18% observed; systematic overprediction at high-speed low-flow conditions. Achieved validation level insufficient for MRL 5 acceptance."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vad-hemolysis-monte-carlo-uq",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "500-sample Monte Carlo UQ performed propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity, inlet velocity profile, and rotor tip clearance. 95th-percentile prediction interval spans factor of 2.3 around nominal hemolysis index. UQ results confirm high sensitivity to tip clearance geometry but no formal SensitivityAnalysis node was registered."
    }
  ],
